<P>
   HACKER-ARREST (Ile Brizard, Quebec) _ It is the picture of
suburban normalcy: a new four-bedroom house on the edge of a golf
course. But according to the Canadian and American police, the
15-year-old basketball player is Mafiaboy, for the moment North
America's most notorious computer crime suspect. From this house,
the Canadian police have carted away computers that they say the
ninth-grader used to sabotage CNN.com, tying up the Web site for
four hours on Feb. 8. By James Brooke.
</P>
