<P>
   AUCTION-SUIT-LAWYERS (New York) _ With the world's two biggest
auction houses as defendants in a price-fixing lawsuit, a federal
judge has come up with a novel way of selecting the lead lawyers
for the large field of aggrieved customers: Hold an auction. Much
as judges seek to make the punishment fit the crime, Judge Lewis A.
Kaplan, presiding over a class-action lawsuit against Sotheby's and
