<P>
   COMPUTER-BUG-ORIGIN (Undated) _ A contestant on ``Who Wants to
Be a Millionaire'' won the jackpot after linking the term computer
``bug'' to a moth that flew into a supercomputer back in the 1940s.
Though the answer is right, the question was wrong. That isn't the
origin of the term computer bug _ but the quiz show isn't about to
admit it. By Laurence Zuckerman.
</P>
<P>
   U.S.-GYPSY-PROFILE (New York) _ Most of the Gypsies in Spokane,
Wash., would just like Jimmy Marks to shut up. He has brought too
much exposure to their secretive world, a tale told in ``American
Gypsy,'' a documentary film by Jasmine Dellal that reveals how
Marks came to be an outcast, ``marime''_ ``unclean'' in Romani, the
Gypsy language. By Dinitia Smith.
