a Nervous Breakdown'' is already the name of a movie. It would have
been a fine title for the Fresh Tracks program this week at Dance
Theater Workshop. Jittery women filled all the offerings of this
latest event in a series featuring new choreographers. By Jack
Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   PARKER-JAZZ-REVIEW (New York) _ Ben Ratliff reviews a
performance by jazz great Evan Parker.
</P>
<P>
   LESH-ROCK-REVIEW (New York) _ In a recent concert, Phil Lesh and
Friends played Grateful Dead songs in a performance that rivaled
the Dead in their prime. By Jon Pareles.
</P>
<P>
   MOSLEY-DANCE-REVIEW (New York) _ An air of youngsters getting
together to put on a show hung over ``Lil' This, Lil' That,'' a
program presented by Earl Mosley's Diversity of Dance company this
week. But out of those homemade materials came an evening of
crackling imagination, hilarity and terrific performing. By
Jennifer Dunning.
</P>
<P>
   TV-SHYLOCK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Does the modern world have a place
in it for Shakespeare's ``Merchant of Venice''? The question is
raised but not resolved by an inquiry on Bravo into the life and
times of the character Shakespeare called Shylock. By Walter
Goodman.
</P>
