</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLOBAL-CONTRASTS-REVIEW-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
  
 LONDON: chronic instability.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In the south of Zambia spindly men, silhouetted against the
fierce light of the Zambezi valley, held up their wares for sale _
a tortoise in one hand, a chunk of crystalline rock the color of
amethyst in the other _ hoping to earn a few dollars. Others held
wads of Zambian currency, fluttering in their hands like small
birds, offering an illegal exchange for Zimbabwe dollars. Even
Zimbabwe, with its intractable economic woes, had more to offer
these desperate men than their own country.
