Gonzalez with his father.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-MEDIA (Dateline TK) _ Media coverage and reaction.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-HAVANA (Havana) _ Reaction in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   DOTCOM-FUTURE (Bellevue, Wash.) _ After a turbulent week in
which a dozen major Internet companies here all watched the value
of their stocks hit record or near-record lows, then spike back
upward, it is hard to find any Internet executive who does not
profess a belief that the market will, and should, shake loose some
dot-com losers in the months ahead. But so far, such a prospect
hardly seems to have sapped the air of confidence that still
pervades many companies here. By Sam Howe Verhovek.
</P>
<P>
   NUCLEAR-MOUNTAIN (Amargosa Valley, Nev.) _ To the Western
Shoshone Indians, Yucca Mountain, slated to become the home for all
eternity to 77,000 tons of highly lethal nuclear waste from across
the United States, is sacred. The land, 100 miles northwest of Las
Vegas by the Nevada Test Site _ the proving ground for the atomic
bomb _ is part of what was once a vast territory the Western
Shoshones roamed, and still claim as their own. By Evelyn Nieves.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;  (Moving in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   EARTH-DAY (Washington) _ Under the banner of clean energy, Earth
Day participants Saturday celebrated in the nation's capital and at
thousands of events around the globe in an extravaganza of
entertainment, advocacy and politics.
</P>
