<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DOWD-COLUMN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: SPITE OR ART? 
</HEADLINE>
   By MAUREEN DOWD   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ We anticipated a New York Senate race perfumed with
romantic vengeance.
</P>
<P>
   Long-Suffering political wife, estranged from Self-Centered
husband, sashays to center stage and crows: ``Check this out, babe!
I rule now.''
</P>
<P>
   But who knew that our spunky heroine would be Donna Hanover?
</P>
<P>
   The mayor's wife has announced she will do a star turn
off-Broadway in ``The Vagina Monologues,'' a feminist meditation
featuring just the kind of graphic sexuality that Rudy Giuliani has
been trying to stamp out for years.
</P>
<P>
   One can only imagine how all the mayor's conservative,
small-town donors from out of state _ the folks he has been
inflaming with letters about the fem-lib elitist Hillary supporting
``so-called `art' that seems deliberately calculated to offend
religious people'' and ``disgusting...pornography'' _ will react to
the news of the Missus' racy new job: ``Hey, Martha, get a load of
this...''
</P>
<P>
   Given Rudy's crusades against the Brooklyn Museum's
``Sensation'' exhibition and X-rated businesses, Donna's decision
to appear in a sexually provocative play certainly looks like a
thumb in the eye.
</P>
<P>
   The play is based on interviews with women, from 6 to 75,
exploring their feelings about their most intimate anatomy. The
playwright poses fanciful questions, like ``If your vagina could
talk, what would it say, in two words?'' and ``If your vagina got
dressed, what would it wear? Leather jacket ...tutu...tattoo?'' The
play also looks at painful issues like mass rape and child abuse.
</P>
<P>
   For Hanover, 50, who has had small parts in ``The People vs.
Larry Flynt,'' a sympathetic movie about the pornographer, and soap
operas (she also has a show on the Food Network), this was a chance
for a plum role. The play has attracted a raft of celebrities,
including Whoopi Goldberg reading a lament called ``My Angry
Vagina,'' and Calista Flockhart and Winona Ryder performing a
segment on rape in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
   Eve Ensler, the author and sometime star of ``The Vagina
Monologues,'' is a friend of Hillary Clinton's, and was an honorary
member of her Senate exploratory committee. Yet Hillary has not
dared to attend ``The Vagina Monologues'' in New York for fear Rudy
would crucify her. Now that his wife is going to star, those
associated with the play hope that Mrs. Clinton will catch the show
_ without any comment from the Gracie Mansion peanut gallery.
</P>
<P>
   In an interview on New York 1 last October, Ensler radiated
antipathy to the mayor, accusing him of ``racism'' and
``polarization.'' ``What Giuliani has been doing to the city in
terms of shutting us down, shutting it down and cleaning it up,
wiping out the diversity, and wiping out what is powerful and
unusual about New York has been a real crime,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Hanover may not have known how close Ensler was to Mrs. Clinton
when she agreed to do the part, but she certainly knew the
playwright's mindset.
</P>
<P>
   The Giulianis' marital deal is as mysterious as the Clintons'.
Hanover no longer goes to most public events or appears in her
husband's campaign ads. She dropped her married name a few years
ago, and he stopped wearing his wedding ring a few months ago.
</P>
<P>
   Everyone thought it would be Mrs. Clinton who would spice up
this Senate race with a delicious serving of connubial payback. But
she is running as an extension of her husband rather than a
repudiation.
</P>
<P>
   She seems more dependent on Bill Clinton than ever. She relies
on his political advice. She has tapped his bank of campaign
contributors and advisers. She has welcomed his help defending her
against what he calls ``the right-wing venom machine'' allied with
Rudy Giuliani. She has vowed ``to spend the rest of my life with
him.''
</P>
<P>
   Some Machiavellian types suspect Donna's theatrical surprise is
all part of Hillary's plan _ working brilliantly so far _ to
gaslight Rudy by getting under the control freak's skin and making
him feel as if he has Lost Control of the Agenda. Did the first
lady's friends help her out by offering the wife of the
sanctimonious mayor the role of a lifetime?
</P>
<P>
   Poor Rudy. He is getting squeezed between two women starring in
paeans to female empowerment _ one on the stage and the other on
the stump.
</P>
<P>
   What better way to drive a mayor crazy?
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
