<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
April 23 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact Gerry
Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LA-SUPES (Los Angeles) _ With support from conservative forces,
a powerful Eastside Democratic legislator has shaken that
impregnable bastion of Los Angeles County government, the Board of
Supervisors, with the threat of imposing term limits on supervisors
and slashing their personal budgets as part of board expansion. By
Troy Anderson. (Will move in the ``a'' national news file and in
the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
