<P>
   BOOKS-WOMEN _ Between them, they had written 11 books, but never
one together. Best friends for a quarter-century, they had actually
only lived in the same city once. Now they'd be living in the same
house to finish the book. What sounds like the basis for a wacky TV
sitcom is the real-life story behind ``I Know Just What You Mean''
(Simon &AMP; Schuster, $25), a new book that turns the spotlight on
women's friendships. (Vejnoska, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
MOVED
