<SLUG> BC-ELIAN-SPECIAL-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release SUNDAY AMs, April 23, 2000  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; ATTN. EDITORS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move to NYTimes News Service
subscribers a special package of stories about the seizure this
morning of 6-year-old Cuban refugee Elian Gonzalez in Miami.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta
 &LR; at the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   All stories will move under the  &UR; General national (a) &LR;  coding
and bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-TRAUMA (Miami) _ Psychologists say Elian Gonzalez is
suffering sever trauma that will cause a range of serious lifelong
emotional and development problems from rage to severe attatchment
disorders. By Adam Pertman. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-DECISION (Washington) _ President Clinton says the
decision to remove the boy forcibly was Reno's, but he supports her
completely and thinks she did a good job. By Mary Leonard and Anne
E. Kornblut. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-GORE (Miami) _ Vice President Al Gore breaks with Bill
Clinton, says he commends the people of Miami and thinks the whole
issue should have been resolved long ago in a family court. By Anne
E. Kornblut. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   TV-CUBAN-BOY (Miami) _ Much confusion marks the early hours of
media coverage of the event. By Don Aucoin. 500 words.
</P>
