<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   EDs: The Atlanta Journal-Constitution Major League Baseball page
will be ready by 2 p.m. EDT on Saturday, April 22.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-PIRATES _ ATLANTA _ Coverage of Braves vs. Pirates.
(Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 7:10 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MINORS-NEWPARK _ CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. _After 70 years at Engle
Stadium, baseball has a new home in Chattanooga. BellSouth Ballpark
is one of the few privately financed stadiums in the minors. Owner
Frank Burke promised to build a $10 million downton park near the
Tennessee Aquarium if fans would agree to buy at least 1,800 season
tickets and 10 luxury boxes. They did and now Chattanooga has one
of the most beautiful stadiums in the minors. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-ALI-MAIN _ LOUISVILLE, Ky. _ A generation ago, Muhammad Ali
was unpopular to much of mainstream America for reasons ranging
from his refusal to serve in the military to his affiliation with a
``radical'' religion to his cockiness. Now, he is the most beloved
athlete, if not person, on the planet. Spend a couple of days with
him, and you'll see why. (Tierney, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
60.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BOX-ALI-MUSEUM _ LOUISVILLE, Ky. _ Ali's legacy might be a
museum/learning center to be built in his hometown of Louisville.
The Ali Center would be more than a collection of fight films and
old boxing gloves. Modeled partly after the Carter Center, it would
teach children about conflict resolution and might even resolve
differences between warring adults. (Tierney, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-ALI-TORCH _ ATLANTA _ Nearly four years after the Atlanta
Olympics, the most enduring memory is Ali lighting the torch. A
behind-the-scenes look on how it came about and why it remains such
a cherished moment. (Tierney, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35.
</P>
