   All stories will move under the  &UR; General national (a) &LR;  coding
and bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-TRAUMA (Miami) _ Psychologists say Elian Gonzalez is
suffering severe trauma that will cause a range of serious lifelong
emotional and development problems from rage to severe attatchment
disorders. By Adam Pertman. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-DECISION (Washington) _ President Clinton says the
decision to remove the boy forcibly was Reno's, but he supports her
completely and thinks she did a good job. By Mary Leonard and Anne
E. Kornblut. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-GORE (Miami) _ Vice President Al Gore breaks with Bill
Clinton, says he commends the people of Miami and thinks the whole
issue should have been resolved long ago in a family court. By Anne
E. Kornblut. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   TV-CUBAN-BOY (Miami) _ Once again, media coverage of an ongoing
news story became a factor in the drama, and once again, pictures
held a unique power to sway public opinion. By Don Aucoin and Mark
Jurkowitz. 500 words. (a and e coding)
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-COMENT (Miami) _ It's sad to think that such lengths
were necessary to reclaim a childhood. But in this wildly unhinged
community, negotiation and peaceful resolution simply proved
impossible. By Adrian Walker. 900 words. (a and k coding)
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY-EDITORIAL (Miami) _ No one likes to see armed men
break down the door and snatch a traumatized boy, but make no
mistake about it: Justice and right were served. By H.D.S.
Greenway. 500 words. (a and k coding)
</P>
