<P>
   ELIAN-PSYCHOLOGY _ The tactics used to seize Elian Gonzalez from
his Miami relatives were lightning quick and successful, but the
effect on the boy who has lived through five months of misfortune
may be devastating. From the perspective of a clinical psychologist
who has treated children for over 25 years and taught at City
University of New York, ``this needed to be done differently.''
(Schneider, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-ELIAN _ WASHINGTON _ U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno,
obviously frustrated with the lack of progress in negotiations with
his Miami family, early Saturday morning made good on her threat to
remove 6-year-old Elian Gonzalez from the Little Havana home _ by
any means necessary. Developing. (Shepard, Cox News Service). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   With ELIAN-RIOTS _ MIAMI _Cuban exiles raged through the streets
of Miami's Little Havana Saturday, burning tires, overturning
dumpsters and tangling with roaming squads of riot-clad police who
fired tear gas to quell the outburst triggered by the pre-dawn
removal of Elian Gonzalez. (Williams, Cox News Service). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   With ELIAN-REUNITED _ ANDREWS AIR FORCE BASE, Md. _ After five
months, little Elian Gonzalez is reunited with his father, Juan
Miguel, at this closed air force base outside Washington, D.C. As
loud protesters on both sides of the issue joined the media horde
outside the main gate Saturday, Miami relatives were expected to
fly here in an attempt to visit with the father and boy. (Geewax,
Cox News Service). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   With ELIAN-SEIZED _ MIAMI _ After five months, it was the last
24 hours that before the 5:15 a.m. EST raid on the home of Lazaro
Gonzalez that were the most tense and riveting. Developing.
(Malone, Cox News Service). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   With CUBANS-MIAMI _ MIAMI _ Anguish and anger in Miami over the
federal government's taking of Elian. Inside the house, Lazaro
Gonzalez, the boy's uncle, is too depressed to even watch President
Clinton during his comments. Outside, Miami police use tear gas and
pepper spray often in controlling a small band of about 400 young
Cubans protests in the streets near the Gonzalez home. (Gonzalez
and Douthat, Palm Beach Post). Expected to move by 8 p.m. EST
</P>
<P>
   With CUBAN-REACTION _ Cuban community reaction in West Palm
Beach, including Saturday evening masses. (Bennett and Lambert,
Palm Beach Post) Expected to move by 9 p.m. EST
</P>
<P>
   SNIFFER _ WASHINGTON _ You may say tomato and I may say tomato,
but with one quick sniff, the electronic nose can say ``vine
ripened'' or ``picked green.'' It can tell if a glass of orange
juice is fresh-squeezed or made from concentrate. The very young
science of using electronic sensors and computer programs to detect
and recognize signature ``odors'' is maturing rapidly. As a result,
electronic noses, which didn't exist until a few years ago, are
about to start showing up all over _ in industry, medicine, even
national security.
</P>
<P>
   (Nesmith, Cox News Service).
