<P>
   SCHOOL-VOUCHERS _ PENSACOLA, Fla. _ Just like 50 other kids in
Pensacola, Mary E. Smith's niece and nephew used tax-subsidized
vouchers to leave the public school system in favor of private
education. And like the other students who left one of two failing
Escambia County elementary schools, they're doing better. They'll
finish this school year. But what about next? If the ruling of a
circuit court judge stands, Smith's kids will be back in the public
school system they fled. ``They knew there was a chance that they
might stop the program from the beginning,'' Smith said. ``I'm just
going to tell them like it is. I'll tell them we're going to pray
about it and appeal.'' A personal look at what the voucher system
has done for kids in Pensacola _ and where the families may be
headed if the program is indeed ended. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
