   OPED/EDITORIAL
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ One of your basic civil rights hangs in the
balance before a conservative U.S. Supreme Court that has been none
too fond of such bothers, but recent rulings suggest that just
maybe all but the most throwback of the justices will be willing to
consider the value of the Miranda warning. (Tom Teepen is national
correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ As I prepare to embark on an overseas
journey, I take count of all my traveling electronic devices _ (a)
hoping they fit in my small suitcase and (b) wondering if they will
work there, there and there. How can you have a Global Economy if
no one has the same plugs? (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist for Cox
News Service.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ (Andy Glass is a columnist for Cox News Service
in the Washington bureau.) MOVES THURSDAY.
