   (NYT24) UNDATED -- April 22, 2000 -- OBIT-COHEN-B&AMP;W -- Alexander
H. Cohen, one of the last old-time independent theatrical
producers, who produced 101 shows on Broadway and in London's West
End and originated the national Tony awards telecast in 1967, died
Saturday at Lenox Hill Hospital in Manhattan. He was 79. The cause
was respiratory failure, said his son Gerry Cohen. Cohen with Cary
Grant in the early 1970s during a Tony Awards ceremony. (Collection
of Alexander H. Cohen/The New York Times)
