<P>
   (NYT17) SHELTER ISLAND, N.Y. -- April 22, 2000 --
NY-ISLAND-SENIORS-1 --More than a third of Shelter Island's 2,300
winter residents are over 60, which is twice the average nationally
and in the metropolitan area. The percentage may be even higher in
summer when the population swells to about 10,000. Snugly sheltered
by geography and sensibility from the workaday bustle of Long
Island's North Fork and the antsy glamour of the Hamptons to the
south, this summer resort island has become a kind of year-round
Elder Dorado. Shelter Island as seen from a departing ferry. (Ruth
Fremson/The New York Times)
