<P>
   (NYT15) CAPITOL HEIGHTS, Md. -- April 22, 2000 --
MEDICINE-MERCHANTS -- Albert Russell, a retired optician and
part-time blues singer, is blind in his right eye and nearly blind
in the left from glaucoma, but with no insurance he can not afford
Xalatan, a best-selling eyedrop used to fight the disease. With
$507 million in sales last year, and the potential for billions
more, most of it pure profit, the four-year-old medicine is the
equivalent of liquid gold for its manufacturer, the Pharmacia Corp.
(Marty Katz/The New York Times)
</P>
