<P>
   Ricardo Blazquez, who fled Cuba in 1967 and now lives in the
Washington area, agreed, saying the removal of Elian from the Miami
home was ``a stab in the back'' of the Cuban-American community.
</P>
<P>
   Throughout the day, the cluster of protesters grew, peaking at
perhaps 150, many carrying signs with slogans such as, ``Bill &AMP;
Janet are communist thugs,'' and ``Who runs out country - Clinton
or Castro?''
</P>
<P>
   Marilyn Geewax's e-mail address is marilyng(at)coxnews.com
</P>
<P>
   For more information:
</P>
<P>
   Immigration and Naturalization Service: http://www.ins.usdoj.gov
</P>
<P>
   Miami relatives: http://libertyforelian.org
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
