<HEADER>
A4759 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-WOLF-COLUMN-LADN     04-22 0970
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-WOLF-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS RUFFLED BY SPURS' PLAYOFF SPOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Lakers enter the playoffs as everyone's
darling, but their path of least resistance to the title got a
slight jolt this week, and they have no one to blame but
themselves.
</P>
<P>
   There were some frowns from Laker quarters when they
unexpectedly learned the Spurs had gained home-court advantage in
their first-round matchup with Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   Apparently, the Lakers were not completely aware that under the
NBA's tiebreaker system, the Spurs were capable of gaining
home-court advantage against the Suns in their first-round playoff
series if they defeated the Lakers on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Spurs defeated the Lakers 103-98 in overtime in the regular-
season finale.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers assumed that if the teams tied with the same record,
Phoenix would gain home-court advantage. The teams split their
season series 2-2, but the Spurs won the tiebreaker because they
had a better record against Western Conference teams.
</P>
<P>
   If that had been known before the game, it's doubtful that such
Laker bench-warmers as rookie John Celestand would have played 24
minutes, or Travis Knight 21, or Devean George 19 at the Alamodome.
</P>
<P>
   ``We might have done things a little differently (Wednesday
night),'' a Lakers source said.
</P>
<P>
   This might seem like a small matter, what with everyone
conceding the NBA title to the Lakers, but nobody worries Phil
Jackson like the Spurs, provided Tim Duncan's knee heals in time
for him to be a factor in the postseason.
</P>
<P>
   Without Duncan, the Spurs showed Saturday they probably won't be
able to beat Phoenix. But with him, the Spurs match up better with
the Lakers than any other team. And the Lakers would have loved to
see San Antonio open the playoffs without home-court advantage
against Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers have lost eight of their past nine games to San
Antonio, including a 4-0 thrashing in last year's playoffs, and
Jackson isn't taking any chances in seeking an advantage.
</P>
<P>
   He already fired up the Spurs by suggesting an asterisk be
placed in the record book next to their championship because it was
won during a 50-game season (maybe he'd like one next to his
championships in Chicago, because they were won with Michael
Jordan).
</P>
<P>
   ``I would have liked to see that Zen stuff work in Dallas or
Vancouver,'' Spurs guard Terry Porter said.
</P>
<P>
   NET SEARCH: The Nets are expected to officially fire Don Casey
on Monday, and the short list has already been compiled. The
biggest name is Isiah Thomas, but every other candidate also has
NBA experience. They are Nets assistant Eddie Jordan, former Nets
forward Buck Williams, former Nets forward Rick Mahorn and ex-Laker
Byron Scott.
</P>
<P>
   WARRIOR SHUFFLE: Golden State coach/general manager Garry St.
Jean gladly turned over coaching duties to assistant Dave Cowens,
after confiding to friends he was tired of the pressures of the job
and wanted a less stressful environment.
</P>
<P>
   Another Warriors assistant, Rod Higgins, is expected to get the
Wizards job, albeit a few months later then he wanted, after Golden
State refused to let him out of his contract during the season.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVELING IN STYLE: Rockets guard Steve Francis earned a early
reputation as a malcontent after saying he did not want to play for
Vancouver, but he's shown a big heart in Houston.
</P>
<P>
   When Rockets ballboy Landon Speijhts said he needed a ride for
his high school prom, Francis offered his Corvette.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm nervous, though,'' Speijhts said. ``I'll be driving 20 mph
on the highway.''
</P>
<P>
   PLAYOFF MADNESS: Thanks to TV, the first round of the playoffs
could take 14 days to play five games, and not everyone is happy
about it.
</P>
<P>
   ``To stretch this thing out over two weeks is absolutely
insane,'' Heat coach Pat Riley said. ``You're diffusing the
competitive edge, you're allowing guys to have more preparation.
</P>
<P>
   ``You're allowing people to almost get bored, waiting four days
for games in the playoffs when people want it now. You've been
making them wait all year long, 82 games, and now you're going to
make them wait two weeks to get through five games.''
</P>
<P>
   Riley didn't have to look far to find someone who disagreed.
Heat center Alonzo Mourning favored the take-it-slow approach.
</P>
<P>
   ``This way you can leave it all on the court, then have time to
rest up,'' Mourning said.
</P>
<P>
   FIX IT YOURSELF: The Cavaliers are more than a little nervous
about how Shawn Kemp will spend the offseason. Last year, he was
AWOL for more than six weeks, with the club having no idea of his
whereabouts. It didn't help ease their concern that Kemp showed up
for training camp about 30 pounds overweight and out of shape.
</P>
<P>
   Imagine their horror Thursday, when Kemp appeared set for a
repeat disappearing act.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to set aside team goals to work on my individual
goals,'' Kemp said. ``I'll worry about the team stuff once I come
back in October. This summer I'm going to worry about myself more
than what's going on in the locker room.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to worry about Shawn Kemp for a couple of months.''
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland is crossing its fingers that Kemp means he will be
sequestered in a weight room.
</P>
<P>
   QUALITY BRAND: Still wondering whether Chicago's Elton Brand
deserves to be Rookie of the Year?
</P>
<P>
   Brand finished the season averaging 20.1 points and 10.0
rebounds, the first rookie to average double figures in both
categories since the Spurs' Duncan in 1997-98, and only the fifth
rookie in the '90s to average the double-double. Only 19 rookies in
NBA history have accomplished this feat. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
The NBA column appears Sundays in the Daily News. Staff Writer
Scott Wolf can be reached via e-mail at Hooptalkaol.com. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-22-00 2310EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
